00:33:04,739 --> 00:33:06,699
Should I leave, should I stay, should I fight,

452
00:33:06,699 --> 00:33:08,259
should I not, what do I do?

453
00:33:09,659 --> 00:33:11,499
And he knew that he could run to God

454
00:33:12,139 --> 00:33:15,699
and he could seek God and God would give him direction.

455
00:33:17,819 --> 00:33:22,639
And a key thing that David did in the midst of this trial

456
00:33:22,639 --> 00:33:24,699
is he had some self-examination.

457
00:33:25,899 --> 00:33:27,419
And he was desiring forgiveness,

458
00:33:27,419 --> 00:33:28,739
he was longing for forgiveness.

459
00:33:28,739 --> 00:33:33,339
And he knew that he could go to God who is merciful,

460
00:33:33,339 --> 00:33:36,739
who is ready to pardon and ready to forgive.

461
00:33:36,739 --> 00:33:40,559
And he knew that God would forgive him this evening.

462
00:33:41,819 --> 00:33:42,939
Do you need peace?

463
00:33:44,539 --> 00:33:48,859
Got turmoil, difficulties, things raging

464
00:33:48,859 --> 00:33:51,379
that other people don't even know about just internally,

465
00:33:51,379 --> 00:33:54,259
just difficulties.

466
00:33:54,259 --> 00:33:55,959
Can I encourage you to run to God?

467
00:33:56,899 --> 00:33:58,879
Seek him, he'll give you peace.

468
00:34:00,779 --> 00:34:02,899
I didn't say he'll take the trial away,

469
00:34:02,899 --> 00:34:04,739
I said he'll give you peace.

470
00:34:04,739 --> 00:34:06,619
Because even in the midst of the storm,

471
00:34:06,619 --> 00:34:08,619
he can give us sweet peace.

472
00:34:08,619 --> 00:34:11,739
You need direction, so I just don't know what to do.

473
00:34:11,739 --> 00:34:12,979
I don't know where to go.

474
00:34:14,259 --> 00:34:18,739
God will give you direction, he wants to lead your life.

475
00:34:18,739 --> 00:34:19,939
When we submit to him and say,

476
00:34:19,939 --> 00:34:22,019
God, I just don't know what to do,

477
00:34:22,019 --> 00:34:25,019
would you give me direction and leadership, he will.

478
00:34:26,739 --> 00:34:30,099
It didn't mean that he took away the issue,

479
00:34:30,099 --> 00:34:33,039
it meant that he gave him direction, what's the next step?

480
00:34:33,039 --> 00:34:36,079
Sometimes in life, we wanna know what's 10 steps from now.

481
00:34:36,079 --> 00:34:36,919
What am I supposed to do?

482
00:34:36,919 --> 00:34:38,459
People talk about having a 10-year plan.

483
00:34:39,299 --> 00:34:40,139
I'm just trying to figure out tomorrow.

484
00:34:40,139 --> 00:34:42,219
Sometimes you say that to people, amen?

485
00:34:42,219 --> 00:34:43,259
You want me to have a 10-year plan?

486
00:34:43,259 --> 00:34:45,939
I just wanna know what to do tomorrow.

487
00:34:45,939 --> 00:34:47,859
I don't have the capacity right now.

488
00:34:47,859 --> 00:34:49,379
Sometimes in the midst of the storm,

489
00:34:49,379 --> 00:34:52,619
we don't have the capacity to think about 10 years from now.

490
00:34:53,619 --> 00:34:57,159
Why, because we're in the middle of a storm, amen?

491
00:34:57,159 --> 00:35:00,459
We need direction, we need forgiveness.

492
00:35:00,459 --> 00:35:03,419
That requires us to examine ourselves.

493
00:35:03,419 --> 00:35:07,299
Lord, is there anything that I've done

494
00:35:07,339 --> 00:35:11,819
that has resulted in these circumstances and this trial?

495
00:35:11,819 --> 00:35:14,819
Is there some sin in my life that I need to deal with?

496
00:35:14,819 --> 00:35:16,699
And then we just seek God for forgiveness

497
00:35:16,699 --> 00:35:18,699
because he will forgive.

498
00:35:18,699 --> 00:35:22,499
We learn three valuable lessons from Psalm 25

499
00:35:22,499 --> 00:35:26,459
as we study David in the midst of this trial in his life.

500
00:35:26,459 --> 00:35:27,659
Let's pray.

501
00:35:27,659 --> 00:35:30,059
Lord, we love you, we thank you for loving us,

502
00:35:30,059 --> 00:35:33,139
we thank you for your word, the truth contained therein.

503
00:35:33,139 --> 00:35:36,459
We thank you for the example of David in this psalm

504
00:35:36,499 --> 00:35:37,779
as we've studied for three weeks.

505
00:35:37,779 --> 00:35:39,619
And I pray that you'd help us

506
00:35:39,619 --> 00:35:43,379
to be able to take and apply truth in our lives,

507
00:35:43,379 --> 00:35:47,979
that we would follow the example of David here in Psalm 25.

508
00:35:47,979 --> 00:35:49,339
Thank you for the privilege of prayer.

509
00:35:49,339 --> 00:35:51,339
We thank you that you're a God who hears and answers,

510
00:35:51,339 --> 00:35:53,739
that you have given us the opportunity

511
00:35:53,739 --> 00:35:55,539
to come boldly under the throne of grace.

512
00:35:55,539 --> 00:35:57,459
And I pray that you would bless

513
00:35:57,459 --> 00:35:58,739
the remainder of the service tonight

514
00:35:58,739 --> 00:36:01,259
for it's in Christ's name we pray, amen.

515
00:36:01,259 --> 00:36:02,659
All right, Brother Fernando.

